## Meeting-Ready Talking Points (Short)

1. The 4 repos are not separate products; they are complementary interfaces around the same CircAdapt simulator core.
2. Arts gives contraction-mechanics depth, Koopsen gives parameter reduction/optimization workflows, Munneke gives physiologic perfusion scenarios, VanOsta gives numerical reliability checks.
3. SAS data provides real-world clinical observables; CircAdapt provides mechanistic latent-state simulation.
4. The core technical plan is: harmonize variables -> reduce parameter space -> train surrogate/inverse models -> deploy RL for closed-loop personalization.
5. Main risk is identifiability and simulation instability; mitigation is Koopsen-style sensitivity filtering plus VanOsta stability constraints.

